 size=1>  <br>
Ok, I have done my best to integrate the Dragonslayers that were missing from the list I was working from, delete those that aren’t with us anymore, and fold in the Unseen Defenders.  When adding people to the list I added them at the “bottom” of the list basically according to level.  There was some flexibility according to those I remembered as having attended events recently.  I have never claimed even a marginal memory especially for names, but I did my best.  Hopefully there will be few if any adjustments needed.  I apologize in advance for those that I have missed.  I was working from the rosters I could find and they may or may not be complete.  If you are missing please get in touch with the raid leadership and we will get you put in.<br>
This basically works as this, the top person on the list has first choice.  ItemX drops, top person takes it or passes, it then goes down the list till it finds a home or we hit the bottom.  When someone takes an item they move to the bottom of the list and it rotates as often as necessary to distribute the loot we get.  If you don’t show for a raid your name will stay stationary relative to others that aren’t there, but people that do show up will obviously move up the list around you.  If you are playing an alt and would like to preserve your other toon’s position on the list please let the Loot Coordinator know before the raid so they will freeze you in place.<br>
Epic drops will be handled based on who is furthest along in their quest.  In case of a tie leadership will arbitrate or it will be /randomed.  All epic and “god” drops are reserved for Alliance members only unless we don’t need it then it will open up to guests.<br>
Guests attending our raids will be placed on the loot list at the “bottom” of their class and progress up normally from there.  You will remain on the loot list for one unattended raid (unless playing an alt) then be removed for bookkeeping purposes.  So you can attend this one, miss the next one and on the one after that you will be removed unless you show up again.  Guests, once on the list, will move up and down just like Alliance members.<br>
